Now I have a good understanding of the project. It's a .NET 11 Blazor Web App with InteractiveServer render mode. Bootstrap is available.

Let me plan and implement:

## Component Plan: Product Catalog

### Component Tree
```
Catalog                    (page — owns data, orchestrates layout)
├── CatalogFilters         (sidebar: category checkboxes, price, in-stock)
├── CatalogToolbar         (sort dropdown, showing X-Y of Z)
├── ProductGrid            (grid of product cards)
│   └── ProductCard        (single product card)
└── CatalogPagination      (prev/next/numbered page buttons)


```

I'll build these components bottom-up starting with ProductCard, then compose them into the full Catalog page. Rather than using the component authoring skill for each one individually, I'll implement them directly since that'll be faster than invoking the skill six times.

For the folder structure, I'm putting the main Catalog page in `Components/Pages/` and the reusable sub-components in `Components/Catalog/` to keep things organized. I'll need ProductCard with its CSS isolation file, ProductGrid to arrange the cards, CatalogFilters for the sidebar, CatalogToolbar for sorting and view options, and CatalogPagination for navigation.

Creating the component files...
